text: @harryreis @EgSophie @nytimes I'm not sure I agree that our community didn't speak out forcefully against the Charlottesville-ization after Pittsburgh. I also don't think there is any accountability to be had by the Administration. Hence the need to hold them accountable in 2020 at the ballot box.

name: Daniel Tarman
text: @harryreis @EgSophie @nytimes I think it's a structural threat to the extent that this sort of imagery becomes acceptable in mainstream media and discourse. It's incremental, insidious and should elicit pushback. Am I more alarmed with what's been unleashed by Trumpism? You bet I am.

name: Daniel Tarman
text: @harryreis @EgSophie @nytimes Yes agree there are distinct origins of hate and anti semitism. There is a history of violence by neo nazis, KKK and other right wing hate groups. That's not what your original tweet said in my reading. We can condemn anti semitism from all quarters w out caveats

name: Daniel Tarman
text: @EgSophie For sure yes. No quarrel with that, obviously. Fair minded, caring people should stand shoulder to shoulder for decency and justice. And against hate no matter it's target or origin.

name: Daniel Tarman
text: @harryreis @EgSophie @nytimes People who condemn the NYT cartoon are endangering Jews?

name: Daniel Tarman
text: @EgSophie But don't pretend antisemitism is enacted the same way across the board... Your logic suggests there are tiers of hate. Depicting a group in a hateful way is a step down the road to bad outcomes. Eg The NYT cartoon should be called out and condemned without caveats.

name: Daniel Tarman
text: @EgSophie But hate is hate. It doesn't matter to me where it comes from. It's equally abhorrent and it needs to be called our no matter where it comes from. I'd like to see people across the political spectrum be wing blind when it comes to standing against hate. No yes buts...

name: Daniel Tarman
text: @EgSophie According to your logic I should be totally cool with being dehumanized. It's just words right? And following further once some lunatic from the left murders Jews due to incitement then it's ok to condemn it equally?

name: Daniel Tarman
text: @EgSophie What on earth does it mean when you say how anti semitism is enacted? Is there an acceptable way for antisemtism to be enacted??? How about just condemning it full stop!?

name: Daniel Tarman
text: @harryreis @EgSophie @nytimes Your tweet is absolutely nonsense. If you can't see anti semitism for what it is regardless of where it comes from then you are either blind, intellectually dishonest or naive. It starts with words and images and dehumanization. History shows us that It usually ends badly
